{"METAMER":[{"def":"Any one of several metameric forms of the same substance, or of different substances having the same composition; as, xylene has three metamers, viz.","pos":""}],"METAMERE":[{"def":"One of successive or homodynamous parts in animals and plants; one of a series of similar parts that follow one another in a vertebrate or articulate animal, as in an earthworm; a segment; a somite.","pos":""}],"METAMERIC":[{"def":"Having the same elements united in the same proportion by weight, and with the same molecular weight, but possessing a different structure and different properties; as, methyl ether and ethyl alcohol are metameric compounds.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to a metamere or its formation; as, metameric segmentation.","pos":""}],"METAMERICALLY":[{"def":"In a metameric manner.","pos":""}],"METAMERISM":[{"def":"The symmetry of a metameric structure; serial symmetry; the state of being made up of metameres.","pos":""},{"def":"The state or quality of being metameric; also, the relation or condition of metameric compounds.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHIC":[{"def":"Subject to change; changeable; variable.","pos":""},{"def":"Causing a change of structure.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHISM":[{"def":"The state or quality of being metamorphic; the process by which the material of rock masses has been more or less recrystallized by heat, pressure, etc.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHIST":[{"def":"One who believes that the body of Christ was merged into the Deity when he ascended.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHIZE":[{"def":"To metamorphose.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHOSE":[{"def":"To change into a different form; to transform; to transmute.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHOSER":[{"def":"One who metamorphoses.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHOSIC":[{"def":"Changing the form; transforming.","pos":""}],"METAMORPHOSIS":[{"def":"A change in the form or function of a living organism, by a natural process of growth or development; as, the metamorphosis of the yolk into the embryo, of a tadpole into a frog, or of a bud into a blossom.","pos":""},{"def":"The change of material of one kind into another through the agency of the living organism; metabolism.","pos":""}]}